olive oil
2 potato
1 tomato
1 tin black beans
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet garlic aioli
¼ cup plain flour
1 egg
1 tbs milk
2 Butter Burger Buns
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 drizzle white wine vinegar

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into wedges.
• Place wedges on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice tomato. Drain and rinse black beans.
• In a small bowl, combine sweet chilli sauce and garlic aioli.

• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat!
• In a medium bowl, combine black beans, shredded Cheddar cheese, Louisiana spice blend, the plain flour, egg and milk. Mix well to combine.

TIP: Lift out some of the mixture with a spoon. If it's too wet and doesn't hold its shape, add a little more flour!

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, add heaped tablespoons of fritter mixture in batches and flatten with a spatula (2-3 per person). Cook until golden, 3-4 minutes each side (don't flip too early!).
• Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate. You should get 2-3 fritters per person.

TIP: Add extra olive oil between batches as needed.

• Halve burger buns and bake directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 2-3 minutes.
• In a large bowl, combine mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season.

• Spread burger bun bases with sweet chilli aioli sauce.
• Top with mixed salad leaves, tomato and Louisiana black bean fritters.
• Serve with potato wedges and mayonnaise. Enjoy!